\"biblScope\">198.18</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(iii B. C.)</date>, etc.; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">φασίολος.</foreign> </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n110395.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> hence Lat. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">phaselus, a light boat, canoe, skiff,</tr_> from its <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> ness to a bean-pod, Catull.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4</biblScope></bibl>, Hor.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:3:2:29\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.2.29</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}